Interface ComparatorInterface

All Known Implementing Classes:
OctreeNode, RGBColorComparator
public interface ComparatorInterface

To be able to do sorting in Java 1.1 as defined in java.util.Arrays (which is only available in Java 1.2 and higher), we offer a java.util.Comparator clone under a different name: ComparatorInterface. Sorting will be provided by the Sort class of this package.

Method Detail

compare

public int compare(Object o1,
                   Object o2)
Compares the two argument objects and returns their relation. Returns
  • a value < 0 if o1 is smaller than o2,
  • 0 if o1 is equal to o2 and
  • a value > 0 if o1 is greater than o2.
